<header>
<div id="instruction">
	Read the writing task on the left and answer the questions on the right. In some cases, there is more than one correct answer.
	</div>
</header>

<section id="readingText">
<a id="clickme"><img class="imagetask" src="../media/btn_examtips.jpg" mode="1" id="1002"/></a>
	<br/><br/>
	<p>You should spend about 20 minutes on this task.</p>
	<p><b>One of your penfriends wants to improve their English at a language school. They have never studied at a language school before and have asked for your advice on how to choose a good one.</b></p>
	<p><b>Write a letter to your penfriend. Advise them about the following: the teaching method, the number of students in a class and the number of hours a week.</b></p>
	<p>You should write at least 150 words.</p>
	<p>You do&#xA0;<b>NOT</b>&#xA0;need to write your own address.</p>
	<p>Begin your letter as follows: Dear...,</p>
</section>
<section id="rt2001">
  <p align="left">Read the writing task carefully and make sure you know what you're expected to write.</p>
</section>

<section id="body">
<ol id="splitquestionList">

	<li>Who do you have to write to?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t1">a stranger</a></li>
	<li><a id="t2">a close friend</a></li>
	<li><a id="t3">a penfriend</a></li>
	<li><a id="t4">a relative</a></li>
	<li><a id="t5">a colleague</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>

	<li>What style of letter should you write?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t6">formal</a></li>
	<li><a id="t7">informal</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>

	<li>What do you have to do in this letter?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t8">give advice</a></li>
	<li><a id="t9">make arrangements</a></li>
	<li><a id="t10">request information</a></li>
	<li><a id="t11">explain a situation</a></li>
	<li><a id="t12">make a complaint</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>

	<li>How many points do you have to cover in this letter?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t13">one</a></li>
	<li><a id="t14">two</a></li>
	<li><a id="t15">three</a></li>
	<li><a id="t16">four</a></li>
	<li><a id="t17">five</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>

	<li>Which of the following should you discuss in this letter?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t18">the way the lessons are taught</a></li>
	<li><a id="t19">the nationality of the teacher</a></li>
	<li><a id="t20">the size of the classrooms</a></li>
	<li><a id="t21">the maximum number of students per class</a></li>
	<li><a id="t22">the intensity of the course</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>

	</ol>
	
</section>

